title: El Nino brings rain to California but won't end drought
text:
Los Angeles - The El Nino weather phenomenon is likely to drench California for some time to come and trigger floods, but it still won't end the state's severe drought, experts say.
Torrential rain has triggered chaos in parts of the West Coast region in recent days.
At least 200 vehicles were stuck on highways in central California late last week amid a deluge of water, mud and debris.
The deluge left trailers partly covered in sludge, while mobile homes were knocked over and houses damaged.
